The paper presents a new algorithm for efficient inference in graphical models, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is based on belief propagation, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses applications in relational models and boolean model counting, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the algorithm is designed to exploit symmetries in the graphical structure, which is a topic in computational symmetry (cs.SI).
